  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The proposed study will assess the ability of curcumin, the active ingredient in the Indian
      spice tumeric, to improve the function of arteries with age. Overall, the proposed research
      project has the long-term potential to influence clinical practice guidelines by establishing
      a novel, easy to deliver, cost-effective therapy for treating age-associated arterial
      dysfunction and reducing the risk of cardiovascular disease with age.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
